## 3.4 URL analysis

Four URLs were extracted, all resolving to the same hosted object with differing query parameters.

**Defanged:**

```
hxxp://storage.googleapis[.]com/vcxbiuouioui/IMd02.html#/redirect.html?syv=<token>
```

| Attribute | Value |
|---|---|
| Scheme | `http`, not TLS |
| Host | `storage.googleapis[.]com` |
| Bucket | `vcxbiuouioui` |
| Object | `IMd02.html` |
| Fragment | `#/redirect.html?syv=<token>` |

### Abuse of trusted hosting

The payload is hosted in **Google Cloud Storage**. The host domain is legitimate, widely used, and cannot be blocked without significant collateral impact. This defeats domain-reputation filtering entirely, and any user inspecting the link before clicking sees a recognisable Google domain.

The meaningful indicator is the **bucket name** (`vcxbiuouioui`), not the host.

### Fragment-based redirection

The redirect target is carried in the **URL fragment**, after the `#` character. Fragments are not transmitted to the server. They are processed only by the client.

Consequences:

- Server-side URL scanners retrieving this URL receive the static `IMd02.html` object and no indication of the redirect destination
- The redirect is executed by client-side JavaScript reading `location.hash`
- Server logs at the hosting provider contain no record of the redirect target

This is a deliberate technique to defeat automated URL analysis.

### Per-link tokens

The four URLs differ only in the `syv` parameter, which includes variant markers (`Out_`, `Uns_`) distinguishing the primary call-to-action from the unsubscribe link, alongside an encoded token.

Decoding was attempted and produced no readable output, so the token does not contain a plaintext recipient address. It may nonetheless function as a database key mapping to the recipient on the sender's side.

> **Handling caution.** Tokens of this form commonly identify the recipient. Submission of the full URL to a public analysis service may therefore disclose recipient identity to anyone later obtaining the sending list. Any submission should be made **unlisted or private**, or the token truncated. This applies equally to the unsubscribe link, interaction with which confirms the address is live.

### Analysis status

At time of writing the URL has **not** been retrieved. Live analysis is deferred to an isolated environment. Given the sample is approximately two weeks old, the hosted object is likely to have been removed. Where that is the case, *"object not available at time of analysis"* is recorded as the finding.

