## 3.5 Infrastructure summary

| Attribute | Value |
|---|---|
| Sending IP | `51.161.21.203` |
| ASN | AS16276, OVH SAS |
| ASN type | **Hosting** |
| Location | Beauharnois, Quebec, Canada |
| Reverse DNS | `unbeatablecloud.us[.]com` |
| Abuse contact | `abuse@ovh[.]ca` |
| Network | `51.161.21.0/24` |

**Assessment.** The message originated from commodity rented hosting, not from an email service provider or corporate mail platform. Legitimate transactional mail purporting to originate from a major consumer cloud service would not be sent from such infrastructure. OVH is a legitimate provider whose infrastructure is being abused. Low-cost, rapidly-provisioned servers are attractive to bulk mail operations because they are disposable.

**Domains observed:**

| Layer | Domain | Registered domain |
|---|---|---|
| `From:` header | `5ibhni.nx8om7.dskpn2[.]us` | `dskpn2[.]us` |
| Envelope sender | `live-jobscheduling-icloudamazffffonawsdd2277.waterints[.]com` | `waterints[.]com` |
| Reverse DNS | `unbeatablecloud.us[.]com` | `us[.]com`, a second-level registry |
| Payload hosting | `storage.googleapis[.]com` | Legitimate, abused |

Four separate domains across four functions. Neither of the two attacker sending domains matches the other, and both use random or brand-imitating subdomain labels beneath the registered name, consistent with wildcard DNS permitting unlimited unique hostnames per registration.

**Remediation consequence.** Blocking any fully-qualified hostname observed here is ineffective, because fresh subdomains can be generated at no cost. Blocking must be applied at the registered-domain level (`dskpn2[.]us`, `waterints[.]com`). The Google Cloud Storage host cannot be blocked at all and requires an abuse report instead.

### Timestamp corroboration

The subject line and `Date:` header both carry a `-0400` offset. Beauharnois observes UTC minus 4 during July. The offset in the message matches the local time of the identified sending infrastructure, consistent with the message having been generated on that infrastructure rather than relayed through it.

Delivery at 10:52 BST corresponds to 05:52 EDT, confirming the embedded timestamp is genuine rather than fabricated. That is notable given that other headers in this message are demonstrably fabricated.

